`.toAssocList` converts this list of pairs into an `AssocList`.

So `RelIO.liftFinf n f` is an `AssocList` where the keys are `↑i.toNat` (which are just natural numbers) and the values are `f i` (which are `RelIO S`).

The definition of `AssocList.contains` is that `ident` is one of the keys in the list. So `h` is saying that `ident` is one of the `↑i.toNat` values.

